<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-03-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="253" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-03-01"><hi rend="italic">March 1,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 458.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 883, of the 18th ultimo, and approve your note to the Haitian
                            foreign office in regard to the imposition of higher duties on American
                            than on French tonnage. You will continue to press the matter.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>